As from January, members of the opposite sex will no longer be allowed to board the same commercial tricycles in Kano State. Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, who spoke at the closing ceremony of the 77th annual Islamic Vacation Course, (IVC), organised by Zone A of the Muslim Society of Nigeria (MSSN), held at Bayero University, Kano, said the directive would take effect from next month. Ganduje, represented by the Commander- General of Hisbah Board, Harun lbn- sins, said that the measure was meant to uphold Islamic values and curb immorality.